{"version":"NotebookV1","origId":3366858372929093,"name":"02_fire_metrics","language":"python","commands":[{"version":"CommandV1","origId":3366858372929098,"guid":"26bc3820-6ac8-4c0f-818d-3c870bf0ae35","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":2.0,"command":"%md\n# Pipeline monitoring\nIn the previous notebook, we demonstrated how to ingest, clean and process raw data used in the transmission of regulatory reports. We stored high quality data to a silver table and invalid records to quarantine. Although data quality metrics are available from the job interface, we demonstrate how organizations can programmatically access those metrics into an operational datastore.\n\n[![DLT](https://img.shields.io/badge/-DLT-grey)]()\n[![DLT](https://img.shields.io/badge/-AUTO_LOADER-grey)]()\n[![DLT](https://img.shields.io/badge/-DELTA_SHARING-grey)]()","commandVersion":16,"state":"finished","results":{"type":"raw","data":"","arguments":{},"metadata":{}},"errorSummary":null,"errorTraceType":null,"error":null,"workflows":[],"startTime":0,"submitTime":0,"finishTime":0,"collapsed":false,"bindings":{},"inputWidgets":{},"displayType":"table","width":"auto","height":"auto","xColumns":[],"yColumns":[],"pivotColumns":[],"pivotAggregation":null,"useConsistentColors":false,"customPlotOptions":{},"commentThread":[],"commentsVisible":false,"parentHierarchy":[],"diffInserts":[],"diffDeletes":[],"globalVars":{},"latestUser":"a user","latestUserId":null,"commandTitle":"","showCommandTitle":false,"hideCommandCode":false,"hideCommandResult":false,"isLockedInExamMode":false,"iPythonMetadata":null,"streamStates":{},"datasetPreviewNameToCmdIdMap":{},"tableResultSubCmdIds":[],"nuid":"f35f84bf-4f8a-46f8-afed-6bc9eabe3fb3"},{"version":"CommandV1","origId":3366858372929103,"guid":"12dffc12-1c06-4683-b2ff-a2faf1fbda19","subtype":"command","commandType":"auto","position":3.0,"command":"fire_entity = getParam(\"fire_entity\")\npipeline_dir = getParam(\"pipeline_dir\")\ndata_sharing_path = getParam